        <page n="04" image="pa.fr.fr.1859.0..04">
            <div type="a">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>none</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"The Spirit has turned tail to Gov. Packer. The Governor is gone now, sure.
                    With the aid of Judge Black,the Spirit doubtless will teem with abuse of the
                    best Governor the Locofoco party has given to the State for an age."</excerpt>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Packer</ln>
                        <fn>William</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Gov.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln/>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Repository aruges that Governor Packer will not "howl for slavery," hence
                    he is unpopular with the Buchanan administration and its loyal mouthpiece the
                    Valley Spirit.</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>5</column>
                <head>none</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"A convention of delegates from members of the Democratic party who
                    repudiate the principles of the tyrannical Buchanan administration, will meet in
                    Harrisburg today. The State at large will be represented in it. Fifty delegates
                    from Berks county will attend it. The cause of Gov. Packer is being sustained
                    with much enthusiasm by the Democracy of Pennsylvania. They seem determined that
                    he shall not be insulted by the office-holding faction, with impunity. They
                    exhibit a proper spirit."</excerpt>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Packer</ln>
                        <fn>William</fn>
                        <sf>Gov.</sf>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln/>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>For full transcript of brief article see above.</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
